detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when the PE task has completed initialization.

The first d field contains the application major version defined in PE_MAJOR_VERSION. The second d field contains the application minor version defined in PE_MINOR_VERSION. The third d field contains the application revision number defined in PE_REVISION. The fourth d field contains the application revision number defined in PE_MISSION_REV.

Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task receives a NoOp command.

The first u field contains the application major version defined in PE_MAJOR_VERSION. The first d field contains the application major version defined in PE_MAJOR_VERSION. The second d field contains the application minor version defined in PE_MINOR_VERSION. The third d field contains the application revision number defined in PE_REVISION. The fourth d field contains the application revision number defined in PE_MISSION_REV.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task fails to subscribe to a message at initialization.
The first s field contains the name of the pipe. The second s field contains the macro name of the message. The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task fails to create a CFE Software Bus pipe at initialization.
The s field contains the name of the pipe. The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE CFE_TBL_Manage function.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE CFE_TBL_GetAddress function.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task has had an error reading from a pipe.
The s field contains the name of the pipe. The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task has received an invalid message ID.
The s field contains the name of the pipe. The 16 bit hexadecimal number is the actual message ID received.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task has received an invalid message ID.
The u field contains the actual command code received.

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PETask has received a message with an invalid length.
The first d field contains the message ID. The second d field contains the command code. The third d field contains the actual length. The fourth d field contains the expected length.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task fails to register the PE configuration table.
The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE CFE_TBL_Register function.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS PE Task fails to load the PE configuration table.
The 32 bit hexadecimal number is the error code returned by CFE CFE_TBL_Load function.
